        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer621019949" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17698005074754692648">Glad I picked up this book on a whim! This is the story of a master salesman names Jim from the point of view of his anonymous &apos;friend&apos;, who has what I can only describe as a bipolar view of Jim and the women in Jims life. It&apos;s almost as though he hates that he likes them. Now back to the main character, the story ping pongs back and forth between Jim&apos;s past and present. Piecing together his hectic, incredible, roller coaster ride of a life for the reader. Jim has experienced the highest of high</span>
  <span id="freeText17698005074754692648" style="display:none">Glad I picked up this book on a whim! This is the story of a master salesman names Jim from the point of view of his anonymous 'friend', who has what I can only describe as a bipolar view of Jim and the women in Jims life. It's almost as though he hates that he likes them. Now back to the main character, the story ping pongs back and forth between Jim's past and present. Piecing together his hectic, incredible, roller coaster ride of a life for the reader. Jim has experienced the highest of highs and the lowest of lows. Experiences that are told matter of factly despite how unusual they may be. The story tells of his past wives and the new, much younger, woman that has now entered his life. Shis shares his ruthless ambitiousness and although his situation upon their initial meeting is bleak at best, his stories of his past and the possibilities she sees in him spark a sexual fire that fuels them both for a time. Don't want to ruin the book, so you'll have to read it to find out what happens from there. ;-)</span>
  <a data-text-id="17698005074754692648" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

